Alfie, Zoe, and Mark constantly crack me up with these expiration dates.  The food doesn't have an actual timer on it that goes off on the date on the jar and suddenly it's poisonous!  :)  Those dates are just GUIDELINES.  Yoghurt will last 2 weeks after the date.  Milk will generally last a week longer.  Unopened canned goods can last over a year beyond the date.  Opened things that are preserved (like the garlic) should last months beyond the date on the jar.  I worked in several restaurants and took many food safety courses.  The things to watch for most are fresh meat/seafood items.  Those will spoil quickly.  But cooked sausage and cured meats last a long time (ham, salami, etc) until it's opened.  Just a tip for anyone who is scared of expiration dates.
